text: <@U7VNVRSMC> Just read your lovely infect article. While I have a soft-spot for Skittles (and to a FAR lesser degree, Atraxa) I wonder if you've ever come across a Kaervek infect build. With infected equipment on him, he can slow the game or try to push through while retaining burstiness. Granted, not as consistent or swift as skittles or atraxa, but a nice 'out of nowhere' type deck. Keep them coming (The articles--not the skeleton dragons)
Also, goddamn, the poison counters! Hand-bloody-crafted-poison counters. That's dedication.

<@U6LUSCS1J> I love me some Experiment Kraj! Great decklist, man. Lots of synergies to exploit. I always thought that Kraj players had to be skilled diplomats--the Bismarcks of the table, learning how to use a lot of words to say nothing until the critical combat step--giving or withdrawing aid as it suits you. I liked your breakdown of the creature--it elucidated many things I'd intuitively understood about the general, and made them explicit. Fine work!
Thank you and I’ll have to look into kaevek
